    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half lengthways, then wash thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Roll the <strong>zested lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into quarters</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 450ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> boiled water and stir in the <strong>soft cheese </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>lemon zest </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic is fragrant, add the <strong>orzo </strong>to the pan with the juice of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> <strong>lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add the <strong>creamy stock </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy leek orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the orzo is cooking, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain then add the <strong>jumbo prawns</strong> and cook for 4-5 min</p><p>Tear in the <strong>'Nduja </strong>and add the juice of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2] </span><strong>lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until the prawns are cooked through and the 'Nduja has broken down \u2013 these are your <strong>'Nduja jumbo prawns</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is cooked through, season generously with <strong>black pepper</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon wedges </strong>to a small bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> lemony dressing</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-jumbo-prawns/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy leek orzo</strong> with the <strong>'Nduja jumbo prawns</strong> over the top</p><p>Spoon any<strong> remaining 'Nduja oil </strong>from the pan over the orzo</p><p>Serve the<strong> baby leaf salad</strong> to the side drizzled with the <strong>lemony dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
